sql:
SELECT COUNT(dataset_id) AS dataset_count
FROM uploads
WHERE user_id = 0;

SELECT COUNT(dataset_id) AS dataset_count
FROM geospatial_datasets
WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT user_id, COUNT(dataset_id) AS total_datasets
FROM uploads
GROUP BY user_id;

external_knowledge:
- Average score refers to the mean of all scores assigned to each temperature range; 
- Access count represents the total number of times each temperature range is accessed by users; 
- Spatial reference indicates the spatial reference system (e.g., WGS84, UTM) used for geospatial datasets.

